summary: A pregnant woman and a man are dancing and celebrating their decision to have a large family, despite what some people may think. Several young children are also present and participating in the celebratory atmosphere.
transcript: some people think we're crazy for wanting a big family, believe me, I blame me. That ain't the truth. They're right. I'm living like I can make this kind of mess all by myself. And we couldn't imagine life any other way.
